main event: A radar contact was established on a high-speed object that disappeared after 132 minutes of observation. There was also a visual sighting of a large, white, stationary object near Wake Island.
interesting points: The radar contact showed two targets closing together at a speed of 1,500 knots from the northeast.
The object was observed on radar for over 2 hours but there was no visual sighting made.
The visual sighting near Wake Island described the object as round, white, and large in size, operating at an estimated altitude of 335 feet.
The visual sighting was observed by multiple crew members including the commanding officer, officer, lookout, and quartermaster.
The visual sighting was initially evaluated as a satellite.
sighted object: High-speed radar target, large white stationary object
witnesses: Radar operator, commanding officer, officer, lookout, quartermaster
